    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=You convert forwarded freight-order emails to Qargo JSON.\n\nReturn ONLY valid JSON with this shape:\n{\"customer\":string|null,\"order_identifier\":string,\"customer_reference_number\":string,\"pickup_stop\":{\"location\":{\"name\":string,\"street\":string,\"postal_code\":string,\"city\":string,\"country\":string,\"raw_address\":string},\"note\":string|null,\"instructions\":string|null},\"delivery_stop\":{...same shape...},\"goods\":[{\"type\":string,\"quantity\":number,\"packaging\":string,\"total_weight_kg\":number,\"temperature_c\":number}],\"metadata\":{\"source\":\"ai-fallback\"},\"needs_review\":boolean}\n\nRules:\n- If a required address or order_identifier is missing set needs_review=true.\n- Do NOT invent addresses. Copy exactly from the input.\n- Truncate each attachment to 12000 chars; total 40000 chars max (already pre-truncated).\n\nMAIL SUBJECT: {{ $json.mail.subject }}\nFROM: {{ $json.mail.originalSender }}\n\nBODY:\n{{ (($json.context && $json.context.text) || '').slice(0, 12000) }}\n\nATTACHMENTS (first 40000 chars total):\n{{ ($json.attachments || []).map(a => '--- ' + a.filename + ' ---\\n' + (a.text || '').slice(0, 12000)).join('\\n\\n').slice(0, 40000) }}",
        "options": {
          "systemMessage": "You are a careful logistics data extractor. Return JSON only. No prose."
        }
      },
      "id": "node-ai-agent",
      "name": "AI Agent",
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent",
      "typeVersion": 1.9,
      "position": [2640, 200]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "mode": "runOnceForAllItems",
        "language": "javaScript",
        "jsCode": "// Parse AI agent output into qargo_payload. On JSON error, flag review.\nconst out = [];\nfor (const it of $input.all()) {\n  const raw = it.json.output || it.json.text || it.json.response || '';\n  let payload = null, review = false, reason = null;\n  try {\n    const s = String(raw).trim();\n    const json = s.startsWith('{') ? s : (s.match(/\\{[\\s\\S]*\\}/) || [null])[0];\n    payload = json ? JSON.parse(json) : null;\n  } catch (e) { review = true; reason = 'ai_parse_error: ' + e.message; }\n  if (!payload) { review = true; reason = reason || 'ai_no_json'; }\n  if (payload && payload.needs_review === true) { review = true; reason = 'ai_flagged_review'; }\n  out.push({ json: { ...it.json, qargo_payload: payload, needs_review: review, review_reason: reason, parser: 'ai-fallback' } });\n}\nreturn out;"
      },
      "id": "node-parse-ai",
      "name": "Parse AI Result",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [2880, 200]
